article.headline: Florida Atlantic 77, Norfolk State 64
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Carlos Monroe had game-highs of 24 points and 12 rebounds, lifting Florida Atlantic to a 77-64 win over Norfolk State on Saturday. Monroe was 10-for-16 from the floor, helping the Owls (3-4) connect on 55 percent of their shots and extend their winning streak to three games. Monroe had eight points in a 22-4 first-half run by Florida Atlantic, which ran out to a 37-11 lead in the early going. Derrick Simmons had seven of his 12 points in that burst for the Owls, who got 13 points and seven assists from Paul Graham. Tony Murphy had 14 points and Rashid Cann added 12 for Norfolk State (1-4). The Spartans trailed by 25 after FAU's Brent Crews hit a 3-pointer early in the second half, then peeled off 15 straight points to get within 52-42 with 12:22 remaining. Cann had consecutive baskets to end that run, and Norfolk State would get as close as 66-59 on Corey Lyons' layup with 3:23 left. But Monroe hit a pair of free throws, then added a dunk to get the Owls' lead back to 11, and the margin remained in double figures the rest of the way. Lyons finished with 11 points and Calvin Brown added 10 for Norfolk State.
